///
/// "Installing"
@Node "install" "Installing One Font"
 @{b}Installation@{ub}

    Just double click on OneFont.install icon.
    If you'll wish to uninstall you'll have to edit file S:user-startup
@EndNode
///
/// "Using program"
@Node "use" "Using One Font"
 @{b}Usage@{ub}

    When installed program is automatically used every time you boot.
@EndNode
///
/// "Configuring"
@Node "config" "Configuring One Font"
    If you want to patch topaz to be changed to other font then thinpaz
just load the source into any assembler, go to bottom, change the name
of thinpaz to one you prefer, compile it and here you go.
@EndNode
///
/// "Problems"
@Node "Problems"
    The problems appear when you try to force topaz.font to font of
different width (as I use thinpaz.font). Some programs may expect that
the font they open is 8 pixels width and all routines are hard coded
for this.
    The only program I found which causes big problems by this is AsmOne.
So I disassembled it, changed topaz.font to topan.font, copied topaz to
topan and I wrote a little utility, which DiskOpens topan (AsmOne uses
gfx OpenFont(), so the font has to be already in memory).

    There could appear problems if One Font is executed after opening
Workbench screen (especially when booting). It could freeze computer.
Don't panic! The solution to this problem is: Boot your Amiga from other
disk, run any text processor, load file user-startup from the disk you
installed One Font to, delete line where OneFont is executed, then
load startup-sequence from this disk and add the line you deleted somewhere
to the begining of startup-sequence (as one of the first lines). Then it
should work all right.
    
    I got a mail about problems on Kickstart and Workbench v40 (release
3.1). But it seems the mistake is in Kickstart. Anyway, I'll look at it
and if possible I'll fix it.
@EndNode
///
/// "Requirements"
@Node "Reqs" Requirements
    One Font should run on any Amiga.
    One Font requires assembly compiler and include files for compiling (if
you wish to use other font then thinpaz).

    One Font wes developed using A1200 (Kickstart 39.106, Workbench 39.29)
with 203 MB Conner Hard disk (CP 30204).
    One font was tested under the Kickstart and Workbench mentioned above
and under Kickstart 37.175, Workbench xx.xxx and Kickstart 34.005, all
Kickstarts run on Amiga 1200 and it worked fine.
@EndNode
